      "score": 168,
      "comments": 95,
      "author": "theorchid",
      "published": "2026-07-11T22:28:48Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs hallucinate and lack deterministic precision, making conversational AI a poor substitute for structured, authoritative API and technical documentation.",
        "AI builders must design RAG systems with strict source attribution, as developers prioritize quick, verifiable search over chat-based reasoning.",
        "Replacing traditional search with LLM generation increases verification overhead, degrading developer experience and slowing down troubleshooting workflows."
      ]
    },
    {
