      "score": 10,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "carlana",
      "published": "2026-07-11T18:34:59Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Handsum is a specialized, ultra-compact image format designed to create highly optimized Low-Quality Image Placeholders (LQIP) for modern web applications.",
        "It provides a lightweight alternative to formats like BlurHash or ThumbHash, enabling faster initial page renders and reduced payload sizes.",
        "Engineers can integrate Handsum to generate inlineable, sub-kilobyte preview states, improving Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) and Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)."
      ]
    },
